Maybe... he probably thinks
if he appears in disguise

93
00:06:27,916 --> 00:06:30,041
for the first part of the
story it means we won't think

94
00:06:30,125 --> 00:06:33,333
he's cast himself as the
main character... pathetic.

95
00:06:33,416 --> 00:06:36,416
That so sounds like
something he would do.

96
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:38,000
Hmmmm?

97
00:06:39,625 --> 00:06:42,750
I see... so Harima wrote
this little epic, did he?

98
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:44,458
We're not sure...

99
00:06:44,541 --> 00:06:46,500
Quiet.

100
00:06:46,583 --> 00:06:48,833
Now... now...
it's the culture festival,

101
00:06:48,916 --> 00:06:51,333
I can put my feelings aside.

102
00:06:51,416 --> 00:06:55,000
Mikoto, I have to go take
care of something, okay?

103
00:06:55,083 --> 00:06:58,208
Right... moving
on to the next...

104
00:06:59,541 --> 00:07:01,125
I'm Mai Otsuka!

105
00:07:01,208 --> 00:07:03,625
Usually I'm just an average
first year high schooler!

106
00:07:03,708 --> 00:07:07,250
But the truth is, I have
a secret I can't tell anyone!

107
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:09,541
Charm up, my "Mai" dream!

108
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,250
I'm a magic girl!
And I have special powers.

109
00:07:17,166 --> 00:07:20,375
You know Mai, you would
be a good magic girl.

110
00:07:20,458 --> 00:07:21,916
Whatever! Shut-up!

111
00:07:28,166 --> 00:07:30,541
Let's think about it over night.

112
00:07:30,625 --> 00:07:33,125
It's gonna be hard
pulling all this together...

113
00:07:33,208 --> 00:07:35,750
there must be someone
who's good at doing this.

114
00:07:37,291 --> 00:07:38,916
Takano, you're still here.

115
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,916
Huh...? Yeah.

116
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,875
Heyyy... Have you noticed that
Takano really likes reading?

117
00:07:44,958 --> 00:07:47,833
Yeah, she'd be perfect
for this. She's so smart!

118
00:07:47,916 --> 00:07:51,166
And she never panics...
she's like, got it all...

119
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:54,875
"brains and beauty"...!
She's so cool!

120
00:07:57,333 --> 00:07:59,541
What do you think...
should we ask her?

121
00:08:01,541 --> 00:08:02,833
Hm?

122
00:08:02,916 --> 00:08:04,208
Listen, Takano... would
you like to write the script

123
00:08:04,291 --> 00:08:05,541
for the class play?

124
00:08:05,625 --> 00:08:07,458
You can do it!

125
00:08:07,541 --> 00:08:10,250
In fact... you're
the only person who can!

126
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:12,208
Mm... but I...

127
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:13,833
Hey, it's a good offer.

128
00:08:13,916 --> 00:08:16,500
You should totally do it.

129
00:08:16,583 --> 00:08:18,166
Easy for you to say...

130
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:19,958
I'm no good at
dealing with this.

131
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:23,291
Don't be silly... You're just
letting yourself get tense.

132
00:08:23,375 --> 00:08:25,416
You're usually the
one with that problem.

133
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:27,500
When'd you become Miss Mellow?

134
00:08:27,583 --> 00:08:29,500
I've always been mellow!

135
00:08:30,833 --> 00:08:32,208
But seriously...

136
00:08:32,291 --> 00:08:35,666
You'd be great...
So just do it, okay.

137
00:08:39,041 --> 00:08:40,583
Yeah, I guess you're right.

138
00:08:40,666 --> 00:08:43,583
Wow... I don't think I've
ever seen you smile before.

139
00:08:43,666 --> 00:08:46,791
It's weird... it makes you look
like you're up to something.

140
00:08:46,875 --> 00:08:48,208
It does not.

141
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:49,333
I'm not kidding...

142
00:08:49,416 --> 00:08:51,125
it's really creepy.

143
00:08:52,208 --> 00:08:54,791
This is what we collected
today and yesterday.

144
00:08:54,875 --> 00:08:56,291
All you have to do is write

145
00:08:56,375 --> 00:08:59,041
a script based on
the stories you like.

146
00:08:59,125 --> 00:09:00,666
All right.

147
00:09:03,375 --> 00:09:05,875
Hmm... What's this?

148
00:09:09,125 --> 00:09:11,541
Once upon a time
there was a girl

149
00:09:11,625 --> 00:09:14,208
who was very anti-social.

150
00:09:14,291 --> 00:09:18,666
Her grades were good but
she was a mischief maker...

151
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:22,833
she was rebellious and
a tease... however...

152
00:09:22,916 --> 00:09:25,958
she had some
extraordinary talents.

153
00:09:26,041 --> 00:09:29,625
She liked to read and
loved to write stories...

154
00:09:29,708 --> 00:09:31,166
she even wrote a
play for her class

155
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:33,958
to perform at the
culture festival.

156
00:09:35,041 --> 00:09:37,833
Her classmates were
grateful for her talents

157
00:09:37,916 --> 00:09:40,750
and she lived
happily ever after.

158
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:45,375
Must be Eri...

159
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:51,041
Good friend,
but horrible writer.

160
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:52,875
Hey, Harima!

161
00:09:52,958 --> 00:09:53,916
Huh?

162
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,166
Uh, soba noodles?

163
00:09:55,250 --> 00:09:56,333
Huh?

164
00:09:56,416 --> 00:09:57,458
Please forgive me
for not understanding

165
00:09:57,541 --> 00:09:59,250
what it's like to be
poor and helpless!

166
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:01,375
I don't have any idea
what you're talking about!

167
00:10:01,458 --> 00:10:02,833
You do too!

168
00:10:03,375 --> 00:10:05,916
You're staying over
at school tomorrow?

169
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,166
Yeah... our class
is way behind

170
00:10:08,250 --> 00:10:10,750
on getting ready for
the culture festival.

171
00:10:12,291 --> 00:10:14,375
Oh, are you worried
about Harima?

172
00:10:15,666 --> 00:10:19,208
It's all right, don't worry,
just leave it to your sister!

173
00:10:19,291 --> 00:10:21,916
Huh...? What are
you talking about?

174
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,291
Thanks for dinner!

175
00:10:24,375 --> 00:10:26,875
What did she mean by that?

176
00:10:29,208 --> 00:10:30,250
Huhhh?!

177
00:10:30,333 --> 00:10:31,833
It's simple really...

178
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:34,291
you just ask Harima what sort
of things he likes and what his

179
00:10:34,375 --> 00:10:36,625
favorite type of girl is
and all that sort of stuff...

180
00:10:36,708 --> 00:10:38,208
If I did it, he'd know
I was up to something,

181
00:10:38,291 --> 00:10:40,708
but it'd sound
natural coming from you!

182
00:10:40,791 --> 00:10:43,375
Are you crazy? No!

183
00:10:44,708 --> 00:10:46,625
You really don't
like Harima, do you?

184
00:10:46,708 --> 00:10:48,083
No, Tenma! Not even remotely!

185
00:10:48,166 --> 00:10:49,583
And what brought this
on all of a sudden?

186
00:10:49,666 --> 00:10:53,208
Mm...! Actually, I'm trying
to find out for Yakumo!

187
00:10:53,291 --> 00:10:54,958
You know, she's so shy...!

188
00:10:55,041 --> 00:10:56,833
But for the invincible
battle ship Eri,

189
00:10:56,916 --> 00:10:58,916
this would be
a piece of cake!

190
00:10:59,000 --> 00:10:59,916
Okay, thanks a lot!

191
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,375
Wait a minute!

192
00:11:03,375 --> 00:11:04,625
Wh... what do I do?

193
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:09,750
Uh, hey, Whiskers...

194
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:10,916
Huh?

195
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,041
Uh, yeah, hi,
I'm doing a questionnaire

196
00:11:12,125 --> 00:11:13,208
for the coffee shop
menu and I wonder

197
00:11:13,291 --> 00:11:14,583
if you could take a
minute of your time

198
00:11:14,666 --> 00:11:16,458
to tell me a little
about your preferences.

199
00:11:16,541 --> 00:11:18,833
Huh...? Sure, I guess.

200
00:11:18,916 --> 00:11:20,750
All right... Good job, Eri!

201
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:22,291
You're... kidding.

202
00:11:22,375 --> 00:11:23,750
Generally speaking,
do you like girls

203
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:25,791
who know how to cook, yes or no?

204
00:11:25,875 --> 00:11:27,125
What?!

205
00:11:27,208 --> 00:11:29,416
That has nothing to do
with the coffee shop menu!

206
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:31,041
Eri must be trippin', yo!

207
00:11:32,666 --> 00:11:34,333
No...! As long as there's love,

208
00:11:34,416 --> 00:11:36,083
cold noodles in a
cup would be fine!

209
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:36,875
I can't believe it.

210
00:11:36,958 --> 00:11:38,250
He actually fell for it.

211
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:41,791
Good one, Eri...! I sure
picked the right girl, huh?

212
00:11:41,875 --> 00:11:43,125
No comment!

213
00:11:43,208 --> 00:11:44,458
Okay, next question.

214
00:11:44,541 --> 00:11:45,250
Shoot.

215
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:46,791
Which do you like better,

216
00:11:46,875 --> 00:11:49,708
a girl who's good at
sports or one who isn't?

217
00:11:49,791 --> 00:11:51,291
Either one would be fine...

218
00:11:51,375 --> 00:11:54,333
oh, but it might be cute
if she couldn't swim.

219
00:11:56,541 --> 00:11:58,750
He couldn't mean...?

220
00:11:58,833 --> 00:12:00,500
Uh... next question, Whiskers...

221
00:12:00,583 --> 00:12:02,166
I mean, Harima...

222
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:03,333
Can you tell me what

223
00:12:03,416 --> 00:12:05,833
kind of hair style
you like a girl to have?

224
00:12:06,541 --> 00:12:09,250
Once again, that has
nothing to do with menu!

225
00:12:09,333 --> 00:12:11,958
That's true, but it's
not like he'll notice.

226
00:12:13,458 --> 00:12:14,375
Wait a minute!

227
00:12:14,458 --> 00:12:16,000
That's Tenma back there...!

228
00:12:16,083 --> 00:12:18,083
So that's it! Now I get it!

229
00:12:18,166 --> 00:12:21,166
She wants to know what
I like...! Heh, heh, heh...!

230
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:26,500
Silly girl, naturally
I like everything about you!

231
00:12:26,583 --> 00:12:28,541
Hm...! That's a real easy one!

232
00:12:28,625 --> 00:12:31,958
I like girls with
squirrelly lookin' pigtails.

233
00:12:32,041 --> 00:12:33,708
Can you feel my love, Tenma?

234
00:12:37,416 --> 00:12:39,041
Hey... you listening?

235
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,750
Does he mean it...? He said...

236
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:50,750
he said he wasn't
seeing anyone, so...

237
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:52,708
So then you must mean...?

238
00:12:52,791 --> 00:12:56,083
Pig tails... I'm a fiend!

239
00:12:56,166 --> 00:12:57,375
Hey, sis...

240
00:12:57,458 --> 00:12:58,375
You forgot your things.

241
00:12:58,458 --> 00:12:59,875
Huh?

242
00:13:03,416 --> 00:13:05,375
Good thinking... Yakumo!

243
00:13:05,458 --> 00:13:07,500
What...? What are
you talking about?

244
00:13:08,208 --> 00:13:10,875
Everybody... we're heading
over to the bath house.

245
00:13:10,958 --> 00:13:12,250
Huh?

246
00:13:14,458 --> 00:13:17,708
Woo-hooo...! It's huge!

247
00:13:17,791 --> 00:13:19,250
There it is.

248
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:22,750
The girls will be right next
door in the next room, naked.

249
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:24,041
We may not be able to see them,

250
00:13:24,125 --> 00:13:26,375
but still, this is,
without a doubt...

251
00:13:26,458 --> 00:13:27,916
Paradise!

252
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:34,416
Oh hey... What?

253
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:35,541
You surprised to see me?

254
00:13:35,625 --> 00:13:37,750
My family owns this bathhouse.

255
00:13:43,250 --> 00:13:44,916
Come on and strip down everyone.

256
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,750
Relax, I've seen
it all before...

257
00:13:47,833 --> 00:13:49,958
